Entry.Value: Develops weapons and items. More equipment becomes available for development as the unit's level increases.

Conducts materials procurement, providing a regular income of materials. The amount of materials procured increases with the unit's level, while materials processing time decreases. Also allows to you build new platforms and expand your base.

Provides support in the area of operations via weapon/ammo supply drops and airstrikes. As unit level increases, the types of attacks available increase, and response time becomes shorter. Fulton success rate during bad weather also improves.

Scouts for the enemy in the area of operations. As the unit's level increases, intel reports become more detailed and more frequent. Reports on locations of dumpsters, back roads, and other points of interest are also added.
Hiring out combat units provides Mother Base with extra sources of GMP. More GMP is accrued as the unit's level increases, and even more GMP can be earned by deploying units on dispatch missions.
Provides security for base facilities. As unit level increases, better security devices become available for development.
Treats sick and injured staff members. As unit level increases, the recovery time for patients decreases. Success rate for Fulton extracting injured personnel will also increase.
Area for unassigned staff awaiting placement into a unit.
Sick or injured staff are placed here to undergo treatment.
Confines soldiers requiring disciplinary action as well as reluctant recruits.
Multipurpose light transport vehicle. A four-wheel drive vehicle built for harsh Russian weather and road conditions. Exported around the world.
Light assault transport vehicle. Has good traversal capability and general versatility. In addition to the U.S. military version, licensed versions are produced around the world.
Multipurpose transport truck. Its 6x6 all-wheel drive gives it great traversal and transport capability, and it has become firmly established as the Soviet Army's truck of choice.
Operational frontline support carrier truck. An all-wheel drive truck used by European as well as American forces. Serves a key role in delivering supplies to the front line.
Armored personnel carrier. Used by many Eastern Bloc forces, mainly to transport troops. Equipped with a 30mm heavy cannon turret.
Reconnaissance vehicle. Armored vehicle used by many Western forces, mainly for reconnaissance missions. Equipped with a 20mm cannon turret.
Self-propelled multiple rocket launcher. An armored vehicle equipped with a multiple launch rocket system. Capable of attacking a wide area by firing a continuous barrage of 130mm rockets.
Fire support armored vehicle. A mobile fighting vehicle developed to provide fire support and equipped with a 105mm tank gun. Its defensive capability is weaker than that of a tank.
All-purpose model main battle tank. Used by Eastern Bloc countries. Sacrifices defensive capability for easier mass production, but is equipped with a powerful 125mm tank gun.
Assault model main battle tank. A well-balanced tank used by Western forces. Dubbed an "assault tank" due to its high mobility and defensive capability. Main armament is a 105mm tank gun.

Heavy machine gun. A machine gun that has long been in service in the West. Being chambered in .50 caliber gives it excellent anti-personnel suppression capability, and it is used for both outpost defense and as a mounted weapon on vehicles.
Mortar. An explosive projectile weapon in use since World War II. Has a simple construction and can be operated by a small team, though it is not very accurate.
Anti-air gatling gun. Outpost defense weapon that spits a hailstorm of large-caliber rounds at an extremely high rate of fire. Has more than enough power for anti-personnel use.
